## When to use
Use this skill when you need quick insights into the top running processes on your system, particularly their CPU and memory usage.

## Approach
Create a custom shell function named `proc_monitor` that leverages the `ps`, `sort`, and `head` commands through the `shell_exec` tool. This function will provide an easy-to-use interface for monitoring resource-intensive processes.

## Example
To create and use the custom process monitoring function:

```shell
function proc_monitor() {
  shell_exec("ps aux | sort -k3,3nr -k4,4nr | head")
}
```

You can then call `proc_monitor` to get a list of top running processes sorted by CPU and memory usage.

## Pitfalls
- Ensure the custom function is added to your `.bashrc` or equivalent shell configuration file for persistent use.
- The sort order may vary depending on system load, so check periodically for changes.